Eolani Jacoby
Eolani Jacoby was the wife of psychiatrist Lawrence Jacoby.
Biography
Eolani lived at the Jacoby home in Hanalei. In early March 1989, her husband suffered a heart attack in Twin Peaks, Washington, so she went there to be with him, notably during his hypnotism by FBI Special Agent Dale Cooper and Sheriff Harry S. Truman.
